\description{
A \code{CompositeCodeSpec} is a composition of all versioned condition components
that collectively define a composite endpoint (e.g., ASCVD). Unlike
\link{CodeSpec}, it does not store codes directly — instead it holds references
to specific versioned \link{CodeSpec} leaf objects, accessible by name via the
\code{component} argument.

The \code{components} list is a flat named list mapping \code{"name_vX"} keys to
\link{CodeSpec} objects, e.g.:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode r">}}\preformatted{components = list(
  chd_v1           = spec_chd_v1,
  stroke_v1        = spec_stroke_v1,
  cerebrovasc_disease_v1 = spec_cerebrovasc_disease_v1
)
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}

The \code{component} argument is \strong{required} when calling \code{get_codes()} or
\code{get_defs()}. The \code{variable_type} argument is forwarded to the component
spec, so both condition and outcome codes are accessible.
}
